1 postconviction proceeding.
2 (g) If a person's right to possess a firearm is restored under this
3 section, any:
4 (1) written court order issued under section 6.4 of this chapter
5 shall be vacated;
6 (2) firearm confiscated under section 6.4 of this chapter shall
7 be:
8 (A) disposed of; or
9 (B) returned to the rightful owner;
10 in the manner described in IC 35-47-3; and
11 (3) valid license confiscated under section 6.4 of this chapter
12 shall be made available to the person not later than
13 seventy-two (72) hours after the person's right to possess a
14 firearm has been restored.
